Parliament, Thursday, 6 August 2020 – The Ad Hoc Committee on the Appointment of the Auditor-General (AG) is calling for public comments on the shortlisted seven candidates who will be considered in the appointment process of the AG. The CVs of the shortlisted candidates have been published on the parliamentary website for perusal. The committee is calling on everyone wishing to comment, to send written submissions to the Committee Secretary, Mr Peter-Paul Mbele to pmbele@parliament.gov.za. The deadline for all submissions is 16h30 on Friday, 14 August 2020. The shortlisted candidates are: ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE ON THE APPOINTMENT OF THE AUDITOR-GENERAL, MS SISISI TOLASHE. For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
